BEGIN NOW How did the father of Millicent receive this second part? END
BEGIN NOW With mixed feelings. END
BEGIN NOW Unsmiling, he heard and saw with wonder a jew's
daughter, all dressed in green. END
BEGIN NOW Condense Stephen's commentary. END
BEGIN NOW One of all, the least of all, is the victim predestined. END
BEGIN NOW Once by
inadvertence twice by design he challenges his destiny. END
BEGIN NOW It comes when he
is abandoned and challenges him reluctant and, as an apparition of hope
and youth, holds him unresisting. END
BEGIN NOW It leads him to a strange habitation,
to a secret infidel apartment, and there, implacable, immolates him,
consenting. END
BEGIN NOW Why was the host (victim predestined) sad? END
BEGIN NOW He wished that a tale of a deed should be told of a deed not by him
should by him not be told. END
BEGIN NOW Why was the host (reluctant, unresisting) still? END
BEGIN NOW In accordance with the law of the conservation of energy. END
BEGIN NOW Why was the host (secret infidel) silent? END
BEGIN NOW He weighed the possible evidences for and against ritual murder: the
incitations of the hierarchy, the superstition of the populace, the
propagation of rumour in continued fraction of veridicity, the envy of
opulence, the influence of retaliation, the sporadic reappearance of
atavistic delinquency, the mitigating circumstances of fanaticism,
hypnotic suggestion and somnambulism. END
BEGIN NOW From which (if any) of these mental or physical disorders was he not
totally immune? END
BEGIN NOW From hypnotic suggestion: once, waking, he had not recognised his
sleeping apartment: more than once, waking, he had been for an indefinite
time incapable of moving or uttering sounds. END
BEGIN NOW From somnambulism: once,
sleeping, his body had risen, crouched and crawled in the direction of a
heatless fire and, having attained its destination, there, curled,
unheated, in night attire had lain, sleeping. END
BEGIN NOW Had this latter or any cognate phenomenon declared itself in any member
of his family? END
BEGIN NOW Twice, in Holles street and in Ontario terrace, his daughter Millicent
(Milly) at the ages of 6 and 8 years had uttered in sleep an exclamation
of terror and had replied to the interrogations of two figures in night
attire with a vacant mute expression. END
BEGIN NOW What other infantile memories had he of her? END
BEGIN NOW 15 June 1889. END
BEGIN NOW A querulous newborn female infant crying to cause and
lessen congestion. END
BEGIN NOW A child renamed Padney Socks she shook with shocks her
moneybox: counted his three free moneypenny buttons, one, tloo, tlee: a
doll, a boy, a sailor she cast away: blond, born of two dark, she had
blond ancestry, remote, a violation, Herr Hauptmann Hainau, Austrian
army, proximate, a hallucination, lieutenant Mulvey, British navy. END
BEGIN NOW What endemic characteristics were present? END
BEGIN NOW Conversely the nasal and frontal formation was derived in a direct line
of lineage which, though interrupted, would continue at distant intervals
to more distant intervals to its most distant intervals. END
BEGIN NOW What memories had he of her adolescence? END
BEGIN NOW She relegated her hoop and skippingrope to a recess. END
BEGIN NOW On the duke's lawn,
entreated by an English visitor, she declined to permit him to make and
take away her photographic image (objection not stated). END
BEGIN NOW On the South
Circular road in the company of Elsa Potter, followed by an individual of
