BEGIN NOW Furthermore, silly Milly, she dreamed of having had an
unspoken unremembered conversation with a horse whose name had been
Joseph to whom (which) she had offered a tumblerful of lemonade which it
(he) had appeared to have accepted (cf hearthdreaming cat). END
BEGIN NOW Hence, in
passivity, in economy, in the instinct of tradition, in unexpectedness,
their differences were similar. END
BEGIN NOW In what way had he utilised gifts 1) an owl, 2) a clock, given as
matrimonial auguries, to interest and to instruct her? END
BEGIN NOW As object lessons to explain: 1) the nature and habits of oviparous
